about.summary: Provides access to geocomputing and terrain analysis functions of the geographical information system (GIS) 'SAGA' (System for Automated Geoscientific Analyses) from within R by running the command  line version of SAGA. This package furthermore provides several R functions for handling ASCII grids, including a flexible framework for applying local functions (including predict methods of fitted models) and focal functions to multiple grids. SAGA GIS is available under GPLv2 / LGPLv2 licence from http://sourceforge.net/projects/saga-gis/.

name: r-rsaga
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.3.0" %}

{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-rsaga
  version: {{ version.replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - http://cran.r-project.org/src/contrib/RSAGA_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - http://cran.r-project.org/src/contrib/Archive/RSAGA/RSAGA_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: c9def9b21e256dca6af805223ec5d07be25c627a4d765b37dadacdbe84873ff8

build:
  number: 2
  skip: True  # [win]
  script: R CMD INSTALL --build .
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - r-base
    - r-gstat
    - r-shapefiles
    - r-plyr
    - r-rgdal
    - r-stringr
    - r-magrittr
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-gstat
    - r-shapefiles
    - r-plyr
    - r-rgdal
    - r-stringr
    - r-magrittr

test:
  commands:
    - R -e "library('RSAGA')"  # [not win]
    - R -e \"library('RSAGA')\"  # [win]

about:
  home: https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/RSAGA/index.html
  license: GPL-2.0
  license_file: LICENSE
  license_family: GPL2
  summary: Provides access to geocomputing and terrain analysis functions of the geographical
    information system (GIS) 'SAGA' (System for Automated Geoscientific Analyses) from
    within R by running the command  line version of SAGA. This package furthermore
    provides several R functions for handling ASCII grids, including a flexible framework
    for applying local functions (including predict methods of fitted models) and focal
    functions to multiple grids. SAGA GIS is available under GPLv2 / LGPLv2 licence
    from http://sourceforge.net/projects/saga-gis/.

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - ocefpaf
smithy_version:
No azure token. Create a token and
put it in ~/.conda-smithy/azure.token
3.7.0
